@NODE WSTEP "The introduction..."

   When I download files from Aminet, I save them in my "Aminet:" directory,
with the same tree-structure as the original Aminet archive. I don't
download the "*.readme" files, so after few days it's a little problem to
know what's in the archives. I thought, I could comment these archives with
"short" information, which is displayed on the right side when browsing
through the Aminet website. Yeah, good idea, but it's boring to search the
informations, and write them by hand - especially if you're downloading many
archives. So, I wrote this script. All you need is load the Aminet index,
select the achive, and the script will do the rest. Simple, but I think that
it's helpful.

   More infos in other sections.

   @{"   Return to the main menu...   " LINK MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE WYMAG "Should I have the PowerPC?"

   The requirements:

      - Amiga :) (tested on OS3.x but should work with OS2.x (I think))
      - CygnusEd (tested on v4.2)
      - RexxMast running (CAF is the ARexx script)
      - List, Delete, FileNote and Move commands in the "C:" directory
      - Aminet Index File (from on of the Aminet FTP mirrors)
      - Aminet directory structure (best do it with
                                    AMINET:util/cli/MakeAminetTree.lha)
      - some Aminet downloads ofcourse ;)

   @{"   Return to the main menu...   " LINK MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE INSTL "How to install it?"

   Installation is very simple. All you have to do, is put this script to
your dir with Ced ARexx scripts (I have it in "REXX:CED" directory). Then
you can install it in Ced, using "Special/DOS-ARexx Interface/Install
Command" menu, or execute it with "Send DOS/ARexx command".

   Don't forget to change the Aminet path setting!
   To do that, load the script into text editor (probably Ced, huh?). Find
the "AMINET" string (line 14 in the script). Change the "DH2:DownLoads.new/"
to your path to the directory where you've the Aminet directory structure
(your Aminet archive on the harddisk). YOU MUST END THIS STRING WITH THE
SLASH "/" CHAR!!! That's all.

   @{"   Return to the main menu...   " LINK MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE UZYTK "How can I use it?"

   After succesfull :) installation, load the Aminet Index File, and execute
the script (choose it from menu or with "Send DOS/ARexx command". It asks
you to choose the source directory, where you did save the new downloads.
The script makes a list of this files and starts to search them in the
index. If the file is found, script asks for confirmation if it's the
searched file indeed (sometimes different files are in the same named
archives, in different directories). If it is, the file is commented and
moved into corresponding directory in your Aminet dir, and script searches
for next archive. If the file is wrong, script searches for next file with
the same name. When the file is missing, script displays the window with
this information.

   @{"   Return to the main menu...   " LINK MAIN}
@ENDNODE
